## Universal vs Project-Scoped (CRITICAL)

### Universal (ALWAYS available, every project)
- **Algorithm**, **Skills** (25+), **Hooks** (5+15 handlers), **Secrets**, **Rules**, **TELOS**, **Agents**
- **Research** — 4-tier, **Thinking** — 7 modes, **Security** — full-tool coverage
- **Docs** — `docs/context-routing.md` for topic→path lookup

New projects inherit ALL of the above automatically.

### Project-Scoped (isolated per project)
- `CONTEXT.md`, `GOALS.md`, `DECISIONS.md`, `RULES.md`, `knowledge/`
- `preferences/` — YAML files customizing skill behavior for THIS project

### Skill Preferences
Projects customize skills via `preferences/*.yaml`. If preferences exist, adapt behavior. If not, use defaults.

